##More than 235 hotels in Wuhan are offering free accommodation to healthcare workers due to high demand for accommodation

Micro-signal. NBWEEKLY

Introduction of function, new media with temperature

Recently, due to the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic, the city of Wuhan, Hubei closed, the city's public transport suspended, medical staff to work difficult. In addition to the Voluntary Organization of civilian driver team, New Year's Eve evening, a number of local hotels in Wuhan, for the medical staff to provide free accommodation nearby.

By Liu Tian, editor | Shen Xiaoshan

Recently, due to the COVID-19 pneumonia epidemic, the city of Wuhan, Hubei closed, the city's public transport suspended, medical staff to work difficult. In addition to the Voluntary Organization of civilian driver team, New Year's Eve evening, a number of local hotels organized on their own to provide free accommodation for medical staff nearby.

As of 8:00 pm today, more than 232 hotels in Wuhan have volunteered to support medical staff and provide them with free accommodation nearby. The Hotel Support Team, formed yesterday evening, in a single day, to Wuchang District and Hongshan District as the center, multi-network radiation surrounding urban areas (such as Qingshan District, Wuhan, Jiangxia District, Hanyang District and other places) to take over.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
In addition to a number of Boutique apartment-style hotels, there are a number of such as home, Geum River Star, city convenient hotel chains. Of these, 77 are convenient urban hotels. At present, there are still hotel applications to join.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Compared with the rush on New Year's Eve, the hotel information update on the first day of the New Year is a little more leisurely.

At 10:25 this morning, Ling Yun posted a graphite document link to the hotel's information in the Wuhan Medical and Nursing Hotel Support Group so that hotel staff could edit the information themselves. At 11:15, Xiao Yaxing, the owner of the group, announced the good news that hotel staff can submit hotel information by filling out questionnaires through a wechat APP.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Hotel managers no longer have to copy and paste in groups to fill out hotel information, and Ling Yun doesn't have to keep tabs on people like he did yesterday.

Ling Yun, who is mainly responsible for the statistics and export of Hotel Information, works in the Hubei Branch of flying pig travel (A one-stop travel service platform) . Because of his business relationship, he knows many hotel owners in Wuhan, they joined the Wuhan Hotel Support Team of the initial formation.

He told Nandu weekly that they communicate with the hotel and medical staff mainly through wechat and nail two platforms. Wechat group is mainly used to collect the information of the hotel owners in Wuhan, and Nail Group is the channel for the medical staff to connect.

This morning, global travel news launched an urgent survey titled "Wuhan's Recruitment For free medical accommodation" to help them collect information from hotels and businesses offering free accommodation through a wechat APP.

The survey includes hotel recruitment tips, donations needed by the hotel, contact information of donations and links to the updated list of hotels.

There are two main pieces of information in the recruitment guide, "As long as you have a free room and the community does not complain, you can provide a clean, independent accommodation (if you have air conditioning, please turn off the central air conditioning) , and your hotel room should be as close to the hospital as possible (if the road is far we have someone to meet the convoy) . "

For the four words "live within your means" , the questionnaire is not only in bold type, but also according to the supply of rooms and whether there is no reception at the front desk made a detailed description. The questionnaire stressed that "not all rooms are recommended" and that one-third of empty rooms should be guaranteed to reduce security risks. And if there is no front desk reception, the medical staff will be required to ensure that the room is clean and the bed sheets are changed to make it easier for the next medical staff to check in. If there is a front desk reception, the hotel staff will be required to do a good job of security protection, do not have direct contact with the medical staff and disinfect the guest room after check out.

In the Wuhan Medical Hotel Support Group, Group leader Xiao Yaxing also repeatedly reminded the hotel staff, let them minimize contact with the medical staff.

The hotel merchant fills in the questionnaire by himself, the globe travel news is responsible for the statistical hotel information through the questionnaire, imports the graphite to edit the document. Ling Yun, freed from the most primitive statistics, was responsible for pulling hotel information out of graphite documents, producing a cloud map of Autonavi and publishing it within the group.

Goethe Cloud Atlas is a map visualization of hotel information. Divided Wuhan into twelve districts. Medical personnel can get the information of surrounding hotels by mobile phone location, just need to provide the hotel with the unit, name and working certificate of the hospital can stay free of charge.

"It doesn't take a lot of time [ to create a cloud map ] and it can be updated in a few minutes, " says Ling Yun

However, the information input and cloud map cloud map export, now also need manual operation, otherwise can not guarantee 100% occupancy timeliness. Therefore, the medical staff will still need to check in with the hotel phone in advance to confirm whether the room is still vacant.

"We'll get feedback when we're full, and we'll make notes on which hotels are full, " Ling Yun told the southern weekly, even though it was far more hectic than yesterday, when it was all about manpower, "Now [ information statistics ] have a more normal division of labor, basic information maintenance update there is no problem. "

Hotel staff and disinfection resources are still in short supply due to the Spring Festival holiday and the closure of the city of Wuhan, although there is a clear emphasis on how hotel staff should disinfect the hotel in the recruitment guide, Ling Yun said, "At the moment, it's the health care workers themselves who are doing the cleaning to avoid cross-contamination, and we still don't have enough resources. We have a lot of doctors talking to us about how to disinfect and prevent infection. "

At present, the hotel is in urgent need of various disinfection materials, such as sealed gloves, 84 disinfectant solution, 75% alcohol concentration, 2000 ultraviolet disinfection lamp, air purifier, disposable bedspread and towel bath towel. They are also trying to recruit disinfection companies on Weibo to provide professional disinfection services for hotels.

Because of the shortage of materials, many medical staff still need to bring their own three-piece bed sets and cleaning and disinfection supplies.

"there is a lot of demand for hotel accommodation for medical staff, and at the moment we can not [ provide accommodation for many medical staff ] , especially in the Hankou area, there are very few hotels. "

Source | NANDU weekly
